                          Resources for Alaska EMS

                         Physician Medical Directors

   Revised 01/06/2002

   Purpose:  This page contains information about some of the resources
   available to physician medical directors in Alaska.

   First Class System:  The First Class System is used by the Alaska
   Division of Emergency Services as a communications and information
   management tool.  The have generously set up a conference area for use
   by physician medical directors and emergency department physicians.
   Click here to learn more about the capabilities of this system and to
   request a free account.

   New Physician Medical Director Registration Form:  Click here to
   register as a new physician medical director.  The information is sent
   to the State EMS Office, which will include it in the EMS Directory and
   forward it to the State and Regional EMS Medical Directors.  New EMS
   Medical Directors are also sent a packet of information and resources
   by the State EMS Program.

   Downloads:

   EMS Medical Director's Handbook

   Model EMS Guidelines

   Model Treatment Guidelines

   Alaska EMS Statutes and Regulations

   NHTSA Guide for Preparing Medical Directors

   Links:

   National Association of EMS Physicians

   American Academy of Emergency Physicians (Has extensive links section)

   Alaska State Medical Board

   Main CHEMS Links Page

   Electronic Mail:

   Send e-mail to State EMS Medical Director Ken Zafren

   Send e-mail to EMS Unit Manager Matt Anderson


